properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 27 at 9:22PM PST until January 28 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
...SNOW DEVELOPING THIS EVENING AND OVERNIGHT...

* WHAT...Snow expected above 2000 feet. Total snow accumulations
of 1 to 3 inches in the valleys and up to 4 inches over the
higher mountains.

* WHERE...Newport, Springdale-Hunters Road, Orin-Rice Road,
Flowery Trail Road, Republic, Wauconda, Chesaw Road, Highway
20 Wauconda Summit, Boulder Creek Road, and Sherman Pass.

* WHEN...Until 7 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 AM PST TUESDAY ABOVE 2000 FEET
